---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

export const prerender = true;
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Use"
  description="Terms and conditions for using SiliconFeed at siliconfeed.online."
  ogType="website"
  canonicalUrl="https://siliconfeed.online/terms"
>
  <article class="glass static-page static-page--boxed">
    <h1 class="static-page__title">Terms of Use</h1>
    <p class="static-page__p static-page__legal-note">
      Effective date: April 8, 2026. These Terms govern your access to and use of <strong>siliconfeed.online</strong>
      (“Site”) operated by SiliconFeed (“we”, “us”). They are a practical template for publishers and integrations
      (e.g. Google Publisher Center). They are <strong>not</strong> legal advice—have qualified counsel adapt them for
      your jurisdiction and products.
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">Agreement</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      By using the Site, you agree to these Terms and to our
      <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>. If you do not agree, do not use the Site.
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">The service</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      SiliconFeed provides news and editorial-style content on technology topics. The Site may include RSS, search,
      third-party embeds, analytics, and—if enabled—advertising, subscriptions, or other features. We may change,
      suspend, or discontinue any part of the Site at any time.
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">Automated and aggregated content</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      Much of our pipeline is automated with human-style editing guardrails. We aim for accuracy and link to primary
      sources where provided, but we do not guarantee that content is complete, current, or error-free. You rely on
      information at your own risk for decisions (business, legal, financial, technical, or otherwise).
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">Intellectual property</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      The Site’s design, branding, selection and arrangement of materials, and original SiliconFeed text are protected
      by applicable intellectual property laws. You may browse and share links in the ordinary way; you may not scrape,
      systematically download, or republish our content at scale without permission except as allowed by law (e.g. fair
      use or quotation). Third-party names, logos, and trademarks belong to their owners.
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">Third-party links and services</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      Articles may link to external sites. We do not control those sites and are not responsible for their content,
      policies, or practices. Advertising or payment features may be provided by partners (e.g. Google); their terms
      apply to those products.
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">Acceptable use</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      You agree not to misuse the Site: no unlawful activity, no attempting to breach security, no interference with
      other users or our infrastructure, and no use of the Site to distribute malware or spam.
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      The Site is provided <strong>“as is”</strong> and <strong>“as available”</strong> without warranties of any kind,
      express or implied, including merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement, to the
      fullest extent permitted by law.
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      To the fullest extent permitted by law, SiliconFeed and its operators will not be liable for any indirect,
      incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, or any loss of profits, data, or goodwill, arising from
      your use of the Site. Our aggregate liability for any claim relating to the Site is limited to the greater of
      (a) the amount you paid us for the specific service giving rise to the claim in the twelve months before the
      claim or (b) fifty U.S. dollars (USD $50), if you paid nothing.
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">Indemnity</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      To the extent permitted by law, you agree to indemnify and hold harmless SiliconFeed from claims, damages, losses,
      and expenses (including reasonable legal fees) arising from your violation of these Terms or misuse of the Site.
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">Governing law</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      These Terms are governed by the laws of the United States and the State of Delaware, without regard to conflict
      of law rules, except where mandatory consumer protections in your country apply. Courts in Delaware (or another
      forum we specify in an update) may have exclusive jurisdiction for disputes, where permitted by law.
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">Changes</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      We may update these Terms by posting a new version on this page and changing the effective date. Continued use after
      changes means you accept the updated Terms where the law allows.
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">Contact</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      Questions: <a href="mailto:hello@siliconfeed.online">hello@siliconfeed.online</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>
